  <h1>
   draw_set_lighting
  </h1>
  This function is used to enable all lighting effects. Default is disabled (
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  ).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_lighting(enable);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      enable
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Boolean
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      Enable or disable all lighting (
      <span>
       true
      </span>
      or false)
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_lighting(true);
draw_light_define_direction(1, 0, 1, 0, c_white);
draw_light_enable(1, true);
</code></pre>
  The above code will enable lighting for the whole scene, then define a white directional light in the room space, and then finally turn that light on.
 </body>
